Symptoms:
- “This site can't be reached”
- “DNS_PROBE_FINISHED_NXDOMAIN”
- Service works via IP:port but not hostname
- Browser times out connecting

Diagnosis:
nslookup [service].lab.local
ping [service].lab.local
curl http://[ip]:[port]
docker logs nginx
grep [service] /opt/docker/nginx/nginx.conf

Common Causes:
- DNS record missing in FreeIPA
- Nginx reverse proxy not configured for service
- Typo in hostname
- Service container not running
- Firewall blocking connection
- Client not using FreeIPA DNS

Solutions:

For missing DNS record:
ssh [user]@mgmt.lab.local
kinit admin
ipa dnsrecord-add lab.local [hostname] –a-rec=[ip]
# Verify:
nslookup [service].lab.local

For missing Nginx route:
ssh jireland@apps.lab.local
nano /opt/docker/nginx/nginx.conf
# Add server block:

  server {\\
      listen 80;\\
      server_name [service].lab.local;\\
      location / {\\
          proxy_pass http://[container_name]:[port];\\
      }\\
  }\\

docker compose restart nginx

For service not running:
docker ps | grep [service]
docker compose up -d [service]

For client DNS issues:
# On client machine, verify DNS server is FreeIPA (192.168.1.11)
# Check /etc/resolv.conf or network settings

Prevention:
- Add DNS record when deploying new service
- Add Nginx route at same time
- Test with nslookup before browser
- Document all service URLs
